    "This is partly because the publishing industry in Africa is largely educational, and decisions are influenced by enrolment figures in schools and less often data-driven and machineaided.",
    "There is however a need for publishers in Africa to take advantage of these technologies as new players are emerging to take part in the lucrative book publishing industry, capitalizing on emerging technologies.",
    "Despite the acknowledged value of AI for the book sector in Africa, its adoption has brought with it challenges for authors, publishers and other relevant stakeholders.",
    "The integration of AI tools in authorship in particular has ethical implications which require due diligence in the usage of the tools (Ngaruiya et al., 2023).",
    "In the same context, Onoja (2023) argues that one of the major concerns surrounding AI-generated content is the potential for plagiarism, and whether AI-produced work should be held to the same standards as human-written content."
